## Styling

- Always use CSS modules (`.module.css` files) for component-specific styles instead of inline `<style>` tags.
- CSS module files should be named after their corresponding component file (e.g., `component-name.module.css` for `component-name.tsx`).

## Error Handling

- Never use `console.log()`, `console.error()`, or `console.warn()` for user-facing error messages in TSX/TS files.
- Always use the notification system for displaying errors to users:
  - Use the `useNotification()` hook from `@/lib/hooks/use-notification.tsx` to get notification functions (`showError`, `showSuccess`, `showWarning`, `showInfo`).
  - The notification system uses Mantine's notifications (`@mantine/notifications`) which is already set up in the root layout. No need to render any container components.
  - All notifications automatically appear in the top-right corner and auto-dismiss after 5 seconds.
  - The hook functions accept a `message` (required) and optional `title` parameter: `showError(message: string, title?: string)`
  - For child components that need to report errors, pass an `onError` callback prop to the parent component, which will handle displaying the notification using the hook.
  - Error notifications should be triggered in the parent component, not in the component where the error occurs.
